comments: Valanciunas (NOP) momentarily applies his hand to Collins' (UTA) side and marginal body contact occurs during his post shot attempt.
George (UTA) moves somewhat towards Marshall's (NOP) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together at the same spot.
George (UTA) places his hand momentarily on Marshall's (NOP) side and immediately removes his hand as Marshall begins his upward shooting motion.
Kessler (UTA) is firming up over his right foot and he absorbs the contact from Jones (NOP) during the pick.
Kessler (UTA) brushes Williamson's (NOP) arm and marginal contact occurs as he secures the rebound.
Marshall (NOP) and Clarkson (UTA) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Marshall (NOP) brings his hand towards Clarkson's (UTA) front and marginal contact occurs as they move over the pick.
Valanciunas (NOP) brings his hand towards Clarkson's (UTA) shoulder and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Marshall (NOP) legally contests Clarkson's (UTA) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Clarkson (UTA) fall to the floor and incidental foot to foot contact occurs with Marshall (NOP) after the change of possession.
Marshall (NOP) steps slightly forward towards Clarkson (UTA) as he is firming up, and the contact is marginal.
Jones (NOP) is moving alongside Clarkson's (UTA) path and marginal body contact occurs as the two come together during Clarkson's drive.
Marshall (NOP) contests Clarkson's (UTA) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Ingram (NOP) and Collins (UTA) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
After the ball becomes loose, Jones (NOP) dives to the floor and cleanly deflects the ball away from Fontecchio (UTA).  Any ensuing lower body contact that occurs after the deflection is incidental.
Fontecchio (UTA) cleanly dislodges the ball from Marshall (NOP).
Clarkson (UTA) moves forward into Marshall (NOP) and initiates contact that affects his SQBR.
Kessler (UTA) places his hands momentarily on Marshall's (NOP) side before immediately removing his hands.
Marshall (NOP) establishes himself in Kessler's (UTA) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Collins (UTA) is moving alongside Williamson's (NOP) path and marginal body contact occurs at the end of Williamson's drive.
Marshall (NOP) brings his hands towards Collins (UTA) and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the rebound.
Williamson (NOP) and Kessler (UTA) mutually engage with one another as marginal contact occurs as they come together in pursuit for the loose ball.
Williamson (NOP) brings his left hand towards George's (UTA) front and marginal contact occurs as his right hand makes simultaneous clean contact with the ball.
George's (UTA) right foot steps out of bounds while still in possession of the ball.
After George (UTA) throws the ball back inbounds, it hits off of Hawkins (NOP) and then Williamson's (NOP) leg, whose foot is on the baseline.
